  "title": "Scientist (High-Speed Analog IC Design) (Integrated Circuit Design and System), IME",
  "description": "<p>We are looking for a candidate for high-speed analog integrated circuit design. This candidate will contribute to the development of high-linearity driver circuits for next generation high performance silicon photonics modulators. This requires the candidate to work closely with the optics team on the electro/optical co-design as well as system integration and validation.</p><p><u><strong>Job Description</strong></u></p><ul><li>Design, develop and validate high linearity voltage mode and current mode drivers, linearity enhancement circuit, variable gain amplifier and the gain control circuits.\n</li><li>3D EM Modelling of passives including interconnects, transmission line and on-chip inductors.\n</li><li>Collaborate with cross-functional teams to create innovative circuit solutions for electro-optical interface. \n</li><li>Work with other functional groups on devising characterization plans and post-silicon validation. \n</li><li>Prepare design documentation and participate in design reviews.</li></ul><p><u><strong>Job Requirements </strong></u></p><ul><li>PhD in Electronic Engineering or related areas. \n</li><li>At least 2-years of transistor-level analog circuit design experience.\n</li><li>Good understanding of CMOS analog IC design methodologies and successful tapeout experience.\n</li><li>Familiar with analog IC design and verification flow.\n</li><li>Industry experience would be a plus.\n</li><li>Familiar with the IC test equipment, such as oscilloscope, spectrum analyzer, etc.\n</li><li>Good written and communication skills.\n</li><li>Able to generate high-quality scientific publications and patents.\n</li><li>Team player, quick learner and self-driven.</li></ul>",
